 This GitHub repository contains data and walkthroughs for a NICAR '14 workshop on using CartoDB and PostGIS for data visualization. The workshop is an introduction to PostGIS and the power of geospatial processing with open source tools, using the CartoDB platform to create dynamic interactive maps. The repository includes a tutorial on how to use CartoDB and PostGIS, as well as examples of different types of maps that can be created. It also includes information on how to import data into CartoDB and how to use SQL to filter and analyze the data. The workshop is designed for anyone who is interested in learning how to use geospatial data for storytelling and data visualization.
